Borno Governor, Professor
Babagana Umara Zulum has approved the appointment of Colonel A.A. Chiroma as
Special Adviser on Security. Special Adviser on Public
Relations and Strategy, Malam Isa Gusau, who made the announcement, said
Governor Zulum has also appointed 10 Senior and Special Assistants for specific
functions, two of whom are to serve under the state’s deputy governor. The spokesman explained that ‎Governor Zulum will soon approve a
date for swearing-in of the special Adviser while all other appointments take
immediate effect. See full list: